<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 04 at 8:27PM CDT  by NWS Goodland</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Wichita and
southeastern Greeley Counties through 800 PM MDT/900 PM CDT/...
At 727 PM MDT/827 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 8 miles southeast of Tribune, moving northeast at 40
mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northern Wichita
and southeastern Greeley Counties, including the following
locations... Selkirk.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
